for i in range(1,7):
    count_products.append(sales_df[sales_df.columns[i]].sum())
#     labels.append(sales_df.columns[i])

plt.title('Sales data')
plt.legend(loc = 4)

In [55]:
from pandas_bokeh import output_notebook as out

specific_years = [1900,1950,2000]
marriage = []
divorce = []
for index, row in marriage_df.iterrows():
    if row['Year'] in specific_years:
        marriage.append(row['Marriages_per_1000'])
        divorce.append(row['Divorces_per_1000'])

data = {
    'Years':specific_years,
    'marriage': marriage,
    'divorce': divorce,
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data).set_index("Years")

p_bar = df.plot_bokeh.bar(
    ylabel="Per 1000 capita", 
    title="Number of marriages and divorces per capita in the U.S. between 1900, 1950 and 2000")

In [65]:
from math import pi

import pandas as pd

from bokeh.io import output_file, show, curdoc
from bokeh.palettes import Category20c
from bokeh.plotting import figure
from bokeh.transform import cumsum
from bokeh.models import HoverTool
from bokeh.themes import built_in_themes


count_products = []
labels = ["FaceCream", "FaceWash", "ToothPaste", "Bathing soap", "Shampoo", "Moisturizer"]
for i in range(1,7):
    count_products.append(sales_df[sales_df.columns[i]].sum())
    
# make dictionary of data
# optional:
# res = {test_keys[i]: test_values[i] for i in range(len(test_keys))}

res = {}
for key in labels:
    for value in count_products:
        res[key] = value
        count_products.remove(value)
        break

data = pd.Series(res).reset_index(name='value').rename(columns={'index':'product'})
data['angle'] = data['value']/data['value'].sum() * 2*pi
data['color'] = Category20c[len(res)]

hover = HoverTool(tooltips=[("@language","@label"), ("@percentage", "@percentage{%0.2f}")])

p = figure(plot_height=350, title="Sales data", toolbar_location=None,
           tools="hover", tooltips="@product: @value", x_range=(-0.5, 1.0))

p.wedge(x=0, y=1, radius=0.4,
        start_angle=cumsum('angle', include_zero=True), end_angle=cumsum('angle'),
        line_color="white", fill_color='color', legend_field='product', source=data)

curdoc().theme = 'contrast'

p.axis.axis_label=None
p.axis.visible=False
p.grid.grid_line_color = None

show(p)
